Class DBView

java.lang.Object

Direct Known Subclasses:
NetworkDiscoveryView, QueryView, ServiceView, TestViewA, TestViewB, TestViewC, TestViewD, TestViewE
public abstract class DBView
extends javax.swing.JPanel

Represents a database view. This GUI panel is responsible for performing certain operations on one instance of one database. Examples of views are query windows, discovery windows, analysis windows and so on.

See Also:
Serialized Form

getSearchableTypes

public java.util.Iterator getSearchableTypes()
Get the iterator of searchable types. So it would return things like "Company", "Service" and "VLAN FNN". This means that a find can be done on items which match certain types.
